Cell.Text: Hello Dragonborn. Yes I know who you are and why you are here - though I sense that this is not mutual. I am a fence for stolen goods. | I travel from island to island in the Sea of Ghosts looking for riches to sell back in Morrowind. | Enough of me, for I am not interesting. I know of this hunter you seek and I know that townspeople in Varghaven have been deliberately deceiving you. | I will tell you what I know in exchange for a small favor. | Aid me in stealing a key from the Karlsen manor, as it is important for a job I am currently working on, and the information I have will be yours.
[S] G|Of course, of course. This is excellent. I anxiously await for your return.

Node.Caption: _IGME_MCA_MainQuest_TheFence_Steal: I will steal the key for you if you can guarantee the information is of value.

Cell.Text: Unfortunately, there is no way for me to guarantee my authenticity. You will simply have to trust me.

Node.Caption: _IGME_MCA_MainQuest_TheFence_Trust: How do I know that I can trust you?

Cell.Text: Then you will find that I am of no use to you, Dragonborn.
G|You're wasting my time Dragonborn, do what you need to do.
[S] G|Quite right you are, Dragonborn. Now get out there and retrieve those boots for me. Don't bother me again until you do.

Node.Caption: _IGME_MCA_MainQuest_TheFence_GetBoots: I have a feeling I don't really have a choice in the matter.

Cell.Text: Tut tut tut... Now now Dragonborn, do not let your temper get the better of you. You know that I'm the only one who can help you right now.

Node.Caption: _IGME_MCA_MainQuest_TheFence_ShrineNo: What? No! I've already done what you've asked of me. Tell me now!

Cell.Text: It's nothing that you're unfamiliar with. I simply need you to take that key you stole and go to a shrine in the northern part of the island. | Once you arrive at this shrine, you will find a pair of boots with a magical enchantment on them. I need you to retrieve these boots for me. | It's a rather simple job, and at the end you'll get the information you seek. Do we have a deal, Dragonborn?

Node.Caption: _IGME_MCA_MainQuest_TheFence_ShrineYes: Fine. What do you ask of me?

Cell.Text: Welcome back Dragonborn, I see you have returned with the key I asked for. I appreciate your help in this matter. Unfortunately I have some bad news. | Something has come up and I can no longer complete a task that I needed to. I'll need you to do it for me if you want information about the hunter.

[S] G|Ha ha ha, yes you are quite right, Dragonborn. Don't be too upset now, this was all destined to happen. You just gave it a spark to ignite the flame. | Come now, let us leave this place. There isn't anything left for us here.

Node.Caption: _IGME_MCA_MainQuest_TheFence_Finish_Yes: This is madness. I have no other choice but to join you though.

Cell.Text: Oh. Hello again Dragonborn. Did I forget to mention that? Hmm. Yes, all of the residents of Varghaven are werewolves. | They came to this island ages ago to escape persecution from the mainlanders. They learned of a way to control their beast forms using that shrine. | Those boots you stole were the essential part of the enchantment that kept them from descending into bloodlust. Did I really forget to mention this? | Oh well, nothing can be done about it now. Will you join me on the boat back? Or are you going to sit there and sulk until you starve to death?

Node.Caption: _IGME_MCA_MainQuest_TheFence_FinishUpTopic: YOU! What the hell are you doing here? Why is everyone turning into werewolves?!
